<math> \begin{align}

&amp;\mathrm{Sp}(2, \mathbb C)\cdot \mathrm{SO}(n, \mathbb C)&amp;&amp;\subset\mathrm{Aut}(\mathbb C^2\otimes\mathbb C^n)\\

&amp;(Z_{\mathbb C}\,\cdot)\, \mathrm{Sp}(2n, \mathbb C)&amp;&amp;\subset \mathrm{Aut}(\mathbb C^{2n})\\

&amp;Z_{\mathbb C} \cdot\mathrm{SL}(2, \mathbb C) &amp;&amp;\subset \mathrm{Aut}(S^3\mathbb C^2)\\

&amp;\mathrm{Sp}(6, \mathbb C)&amp;&amp;\subset \mathrm{Aut}(\Lambda^3_0\mathbb C^6)\cong \mathrm{Aut}(\mathbb C^{14})\\

&amp;\mathrm{SL}(6, \mathbb C)&amp;&amp;\subset \mathrm{Aut}(\Lambda^3\mathbb C^6)\\

&amp;\mathrm{Spin}(12,\mathbb C )&amp;&amp;\subset \mathrm{Aut}(\Delta_{12}^+)\cong \mathrm{Aut}(\mathbb C^{32})\\

&amp;E_7^{\mathbb C}&amp;&amp;\subset \mathrm{Aut}(\mathbb C^{56})\\

\end{align}</math>

<title>Algorithme de fouille de flots de données</title>
<math>t= \frac{1}{\epsilon}\log(\epsilon^{-1} \delta^{-1})</math>
<math>(\Nu, \sum_{k=1}^\Nu \Chi_i^2,\sum_{k=1}^\Nu \Chi_i)</math>

<title>Densité d'un graphe</title>
<math>G = (V, E)</math>
<math>D = \frac{2 \  |E|}{|V| \cdot (|V| - 1)}</math>

<title>Surface cubique</title>
<math>P(X,Y,Z,T)=X^3+Y^3+Z^3+T^3</math>
<math>\{[X:Y:Z:T]\in \mathbb{P}^3(\mathbb{C}) \ | \ X^3+Y^3+Z^3+T^3=0 \}</math>
<math>[X:-X:Y:-Y]=\{[x:-x:y:-y],  x\in \mathbb{C},  y\in \mathbb{C}, (x,y)\neq (0,0)\} </math>
<math>T=1</math>
<math>x^3+y^3+z^3+1=0</math>
<math>\rho=\rho'=-1</math>
<math>X^3+Y^3+Z^3+T^3-(X+Y+Z+T)^3=0</math>
<math>\phi=\frac{1+\sqrt 5}{2}</math>
<math>XYZ+XYT+XZT+YZT=0</math>

<title>Cote Z (statistiques)</title>
<math>{Cote Z=}\frac{X-\mu{}}{\sigma}</math>

<title>Polynôme de Laurent</title>
<math>p(t) = \sum_{k \in \mathbb Z} a_k t^k, \quad a_k \in R</math>
<math>\left(\sum_i a_iX^i\right) + \left(\sum_i b_iX^i\right) = 
\sum_i (a_i+b_i)X^i</math>
<math>\left(\sum_i a_iX^i\right) \cdot \left(\sum_j b_jX^j\right) = 
\sum_k \left(\sum_{i,j: i + j = k} a_i b_j\right)X^k.</math>
<math>a \cdot \sum_{i\in\Z} a_iX^i\, = \, \sum_{i\in\Z} (a a_i)\,X^i</math>
<math>T_{p(X)} = p(X)\frac{\partial}{\partial X}</math>
<math>d_n = T_{-X^{n+1}} = -X^{n+1}\frac{\partial}{\partial X}\,\quad n\in\mathbb Z</math>
<math>[d_i, d_j] = (i - j)d_{i+j}</math>
<math>\tilde G = R[t^{\pm 1}] \otimes_{\mathbb C} G </math>

<title>Régression non linéaire</title>
<math>\forall j, \frac{\partial \mathrm{S}}{\partial a_j} = 0</math>

<title>Bulle (physique)</title>
<math>f_0 = {1 \over 2 \pi R_0}\sqrt{3 \gamma p_0 \over \rho}</math>
<math>f_0 = {1 \over 2 \pi R_0}\sqrt{{3 p_0 \over \rho}+{4 \sigma \over \rho R_0}}</math>

<title>Métrique de Lemaître</title>
<math>ds^2 = c^2.dT^2 - \frac{dR^2}{\left( \frac{3}{2R_S}(R-cT) \right)^{2/3}} - \left( \textstyle\frac{3}{2}. (R-cT) \right)^{4/3}.R_S^{2/3}.(d\theta^2 + sin^2 \theta .d\phi^2 )</math>
<math>ds^2 = c^2.dT^2 - \frac{dR^2}{B} - B^2 {R_S}^2 (d\theta^2 + sin^2 \theta .d\phi^2 )</math>
<math>B = \left( \frac{3}{2R_S}(R-cT) \right)^{2/3}</math>
<math>~c.dT = c.dt+\frac{f(r).dr}{1-\textstyle\frac{R_S}{r}}~</math>
<math>~dR = c.dt+\frac{dr}{f(r).(1-\textstyle\frac{R_S}{r})}~</math>
<math>ds^2 = \frac{1-\textstyle\frac{R_S}{r}}{1-f^2(r)}.\left(c^2.dT^2-f^2(r).dR^2 \right)-r^2.(d\theta^2 + sin^2 \theta .d\phi^2 )</math>
<math>f(r)= \sqrt{ \frac{R_S}{r}}</math>
<math>R-c.T={\textstyle\frac{2}{3}} . \frac{r^{3/2}}{R_S^{1/2}}</math>
<math>r= \left( {\textstyle\frac{3}{2}} .(R-c.T) \right)^{2/3}.R_s^{1/3} = B.R_S</math>
<math>t = \frac {R_S}{c} \left( -\frac{2}{3} B^{1/2} + \ln \left| \frac{B^{1/2}+1}{B^{1/2}-1}\right| + \frac {R}{R_S}\right)</math>
<math>B = \left( \frac{3}{2R_S}(R-cT) \right)^{2/3}</math>
<math>R-c.T= constante</math>
<math>r = constant</math>
<math>R-c.T= 0</math>
<math>r=0</math>
<math>r=R_S</math>
<math>R-c.T= {\textstyle\frac{2}{3}}.R_S</math>
<math>ds^2=0</math>
<math>\textstyle{\frac{dR}{c.dT} = \pm \sqrt{\frac{r}{R_S}}}</math>
<math>R-c.T= constante</math>
<math>\textstyle{\frac{dR}{c.dT} = 1 \in \left]-\sqrt{\frac{r}{R_S}} ; +\sqrt{\frac{r}{R_S}} \right[}</math>
<math>R-c.T= constante</math>
<math>r=0</math>
<math>r=R_S</math>
<math>~c.dT = -\left( c.dt+\frac{f(r).dr}{1-\textstyle\frac{R_S}{r}} \right)~</math>
<math>~dR = c.dt+\frac{dr}{f(r).(1-\textstyle\frac{R_S}{r})}~</math>
<math>~dR = c.dt+\frac{dr}{f(r).(1-\textstyle\frac{R_S}{r})} = 0~</math>
<math>0&lt; r \leqslant R_S</math>

<title>Réseau (sous-groupe discret)</title>
<math>\Gamma \cap U = \{ \mathrm{Id} \}</math>
<math>G = \mathrm{SL}_2(\mathbb{R})</math>
<math>G = \mathrm{SL}_2(\mathbb{C})</math>

<title>Extreme learning machine</title>
<math>\mathbf{\hat{Y}} = \mathbf{W}_2 \sigma(\mathbf{W}_1 x)</math>
<math>\mathbf{W}_2 = \sigma(\mathbf{W}_1 \mathbf{X})^+ \mathbf{Y}</math>

<title>Galvanostat</title>
<math> I_0 = \frac{U_\text{g}}{R_\text{g} + R_\text{c}}</math>

<title>Limite de stabilité</title>
<math> E_F^n=m_n c^2 \,</math>
<math> E_F^n=\sqrt{(p_F^n)^2c^2 + m_n^2 c^4} \,</math>

<title>Formule de Manning-Strickler</title>
<math>V = K_s {R_h}^{2/3} \, i^{1/2}</math>
<math>R_h = \frac{S}{P}</math>

<title>Fonction de Massieu</title>
<math>\mathrm{d} U = \delta W + \delta Q</math>
<math>\delta W = \delta W_P + \delta W_g + \delta W_{em} + \cdots</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U + \mathrm{d} U_\text{ext} = 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S = {\delta Q \over T}</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S \geq { \delta Q \over T}</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} = 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} V + \mathrm{d} V_\text{ext} = 0</math>
<math>\delta W = - P \, \mathrm{d} V</math>
<math>-\delta W = P \, \mathrm{d} V = - P \, \mathrm{d} V_\text{ext}</math>
<math> - \delta Q = T \, \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext}</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U_\text{ext} = - P \, \mathrm{d} V_\text{ext} + T \, \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext}</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U = \delta W + \delta Q</math>
<math>\delta W = - P \, \mathrm{d} V</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U = - P \, \mathrm{d} V + T \, \mathrm{d} S - \left[T \, \mathrm{d} S - \delta Q \right]</math>
<math>T \, \mathrm{d} S - \delta Q = T \left[ \mathrm{d} S - { \delta Q \over T } \right] = T \left[ \mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \right] \geq 0</math>
<math>T \, \mathrm{d} S - \delta Q = T \left[ \mathrm{d} S - { \delta Q \over T } \right] = T \left[ \mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \right] \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U + P \, \mathrm{d} V - T \, \mathrm{d} S = - T \left[\mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \right] \leq 0 </math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U + P \, \mathrm{d} V - T \, \mathrm{d} S = - T \left[\mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \right] \leq 0 </math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi = \mathrm{d} S - {\mathrm{d} U \over T} - {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V = \mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext}</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi = \mathrm{d} S - {\mathrm{d} U \over T} - {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} V = 0</math>
<math>- {\mathrm{d} U \over T} = \mathrm{d} \! \left( - {U \over T} \right)</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi = \mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} \! \left( - {U \over T} \right) = \mathrm{d} \! \left[ S - {U \over T} \right]</math>
<math>J = S - {U \over T} = - {F \over T}</math>
<math>F = U-TS</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} J \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} J = \mathrm{d} S - {\mathrm{d} U \over T} - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right)</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U = - P \, \mathrm{d} V + T \, \mathrm{d} S + \sum_{i=1}^{N} \mu_i \, \mathrm{d} n_i - \left[T \, \mathrm{d} S - \delta Q \right]</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} J = {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i + \left[\mathrm{d} S - {\delta Q \over T} \right]</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} J = {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} J &gt; {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>J = J \! \left( V, {1 \over T}, n \right)</math>
<math>- {\mathrm{d} U \over T} = \mathrm{d} \! \left( - {U \over T} \right)</math>
<math>- {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V = \mathrm{d} \! \left( {- PV \over T} \right)</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi = \mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} \! \left( - {U \over T} \right) + \mathrm{d} \! \left( {- PV \over T} \right) = \mathrm{d} \! \left[ S - {U \over T} - {PV \over T} \right]</math>
<math>Y = S - {U \over T} - {PV \over T}= - {G \over T}</math>
<math>G = U+PV-TS</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y = \mathrm{d} S - {\mathrm{d} U \over T} - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V - V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T } \right)</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U = - P \, \mathrm{d} V + T \, \mathrm{d} S  + \sum_{i=1}^{N} \mu_i \, \mathrm{d} n_i - \left[T \, \mathrm{d} S - \delta Q \right]</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y = -V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T } \right) - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i + \left[\mathrm{d} S - {\delta Q \over T} \right]</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y = -V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T } \right) - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y &gt; -V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T } \right) - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>Y = Y \! \left( {P \over T}, {1 \over T}, n \right)</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T} \right) = {\mathrm{d} P \over T} + P \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right)</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y = -V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T } \right) - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i + \left[\mathrm{d} S - {\delta Q \over T} \right]</math>
<math>= -{V \over T} \, \mathrm{d} \! P - \left[ U + PV \right] \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i + \left[\mathrm{d} S - {\delta Q \over T} \right]</math>
<math>= -{V \over T} \, \mathrm{d} \! P - H \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i + \left[\mathrm{d} S - {\delta Q \over T} \right]</math>
<math>H = U + PV</math>
<math>Y = Y \! \left( P, {1 \over T}, n \right)</math>
<math>y = f \! \left( x \right)</math>
<math>p = f^\prime \! \left( x \right)</math>
<math>x = f^\prime{}^{-1} \! \left( p \right)</math>
<math>g \! \left( p \right) = f \! \left( x \right) - p \cdot x</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U = - P \, \mathrm{d} V + T \, \mathrm{d} S + \sum_{i=1}^{N} \mu_i \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S = {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V  + {1 \over T} \, \mathrm{d} U - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>S = f \! \left( V, U, n \right)</math>
<math>\left( {\partial S \over \partial V} \right)_{U,n} = {P \over T}</math>
<math>\left( {\partial S \over \partial U} \right)_{V,n} = {1 \over T}</math>
<math>\left( {\partial S \over \partial n_i} \right)_{V,U,n_{j \neq j}} = -{\mu_i \over T}</math>
<math>g_1 \! \left( V, {1 \over T}, n \right) = S - \left( {\partial S \over \partial U} \right)_{V,n} \cdot U
= S -{1 \over T} U = J \! \left( V, {1 \over T}, n \right)</math>
<math>g_2 \! \left( V, {1 \over T}, n \right) = S - \left( {\partial S \over \partial V} \right)_{U,n} \cdot V - \left( {\partial S \over \partial U} \right)_{V,n} \cdot U
= S -{P \over T} V -{1 \over T} U = Y \! \left( {P \over T}, {1 \over T}, n \right)</math>
<math>g_3 \! \left( {P \over T}, U, n \right) = S - \left( {\partial S \over \partial V} \right)_{U,n} \cdot V
= S -{P \over T} V = \Psi_1 \! \left( {P \over T}, U, n \right)</math>
<math>g_4 \! \left( V, {1 \over T}, {\mu \over T} \right) = S - \left( {\partial S \over \partial U} \right)_{V,n} \cdot U
- \sum_{i=1}^N \left( {\partial S \over \partial n_i} \right)_{V,U,n_{j \neq j}} \cdot n_i
= S -{1 \over T} U + \sum_{i=1}^N {\mu_i \over T} n_i = \Psi_2 \! \left( V, {1 \over T}, {\mu \over T} \right)</math>
<math>Y = -{G \over T}</math>
<math>G = \sum_{i=1}^N \mu_i n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y = - \sum_{i=1}^N n_i \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {\mu_i \over T} \right) - \sum_{i=1}^N {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y = -V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T } \right) - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} {\mu_i \over T} \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right) + V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T} \right) - \sum_{i=1}^{N} n_i \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {\mu_i \over T} \right) = 0</math>
<math>H \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right) + {V \over T} \, \mathrm{d} \! P - \sum_{i=1}^{N} n_i \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {\mu_i \over T} \right) = 0</math>
<math>H = U + PV</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} J = {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} V - U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T } \right)</math>
<math>\left( {\partial J \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{V,n} = -U</math>
<math>J = -{F \over T}</math>
<math>\left( {\partial {F \over T} \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{V,n} = U</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} Y = -{V \over T} \, \mathrm{d} P - H \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right)</math>
<math>\left( {\partial Y \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{P,n} = -H</math>
<math>Y = -{G \over T}</math>
<math>\left( {\partial {G \over T} \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{P,n} = H</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} F = - P \, \mathrm{d} V - S \, \mathrm{d} T</math>
<math>\left( {\partial F \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n} = -S</math>
<math>\left( {\partial J \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{V,n} = -U</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T} \right) = {\mathrm{d} P \over T} + P \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right)
= {\mathrm{d} P \over T} - {P \over T^2} \, \mathrm{d} T</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} P = T \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T} \right) + {P \over T} \, \mathrm{d} T</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} G = V \, \mathrm{d} P - S \, \mathrm{d} T
= VT \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T} \right) - \left( S - {P \over T} V \right) \, \mathrm{d} T
= VT \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {P \over T} \right) - \Psi_1 \, \mathrm{d} T</math>
<math>\left( {\partial G \over \partial T} \right)_{{P \over T},n} = -\Psi_1</math>
<math>\left( {\partial Y \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{P,n} = -H</math>
<math>\delta Q_V = C_V \, \mathrm{d} T = T \, \mathrm{d} S = \mathrm{d} U</math>
<math>{C_V \over T} = \left( {\partial S \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n}</math>
<math>C_V = \left( {\partial U \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n}
= \left( {\partial {1 \over T} \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n} \left( {\partial U \over \partial {1 \over T} } \right)_{V,n}
= -{1 \over T^2} \left( {\partial U \over \partial {1 \over T} } \right)_{V,n}</math>
<math>\left( {\partial J \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{V,n} = -U</math>
<math>C_V  = \left( {\partial U \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n} = T  \left( {\partial S \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n} = {1 \over T^2} \left( {\partial^2 J \over \partial {1 \over T}^2} \right)_{V,n}</math>
<math>\delta Q_P = C_P \, \mathrm{d} T = T \, \mathrm{d} S = \mathrm{d} H</math>
<math>{C_P \over T} = \left( {\partial S \over \partial T} \right)_{P,n}</math>
<math>C_P = \left( {\partial H \over \partial T} \right)_{P,n}
= \left( {\partial {1 \over T} \over \partial T} \right)_{P,n} \left( {\partial H \over \partial {1 \over T} } \right)_{P,n}
= -{1 \over T^2} \left( {\partial H \over \partial {1 \over T} } \right)_{P,n}</math>
<math>\left( {\partial Y \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{P,n} = -H</math>
<math>C_P  = \left( {\partial H \over \partial T} \right)_{P,n} = T  \left( {\partial S \over \partial T} \right)_{P,n} = {1 \over T^2} \left( {\partial^2 Y \over \partial {1 \over T}^2} \right)_{P,n}</math>
<math>H = U + PV</math>
<math>\Psi_1 = S - {P \over T} V</math>
<math>F = U - TS</math>
<math>J = S - {1 \over T} U = -{F \over T}</math>
<math>G = U + PV - TS</math>
<math>Y = S - {P \over T} V - {1 \over T} U = -{G \over T}</math>
<math>\Phi_G = U - TS - \sum_{i=1}^{N} \mu_i n_i</math>
<math>\Psi_2 = S - {1 \over T} U - \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left( -{\mu_i \over T} \right) n_i = -{\Phi_G \over T}</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U = \delta W + \delta Q</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S \geq {\delta Q \over T}</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U + \mathrm{d} U_\text{ext} = 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U \leq - P \, \mathrm{d} V + T \, \mathrm{d} S + \sum_{i=1}^{N} \mu_i \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} U \leq - P \, \mathrm{d} V + T \, \mathrm{d} S + \sum_{i=1}^{N} \mu_i \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S \geq - \left( - {P \over T} \right) \, \mathrm{d} V  + {1 \over T} \, \mathrm{d} U + \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left( -{\mu_i \over T} \right) \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} S \geq - \left( - {P \over T} \right) \, \mathrm{d} V  + {1 \over T} \, \mathrm{d} U + \sum_{i=1}^{N} \left( -{\mu_i \over T} \right) \, \mathrm{d} n_i</math>
<math>\Phi = \Phi \left( x, y, n \right)</math>
<math>\Psi = \Psi \left( x, y, n \right)</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Phi = - T \left[\mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \right] \leq 0 </math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Phi = - T \left[\mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \right] \leq 0 </math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi = \mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi = \mathrm{d} S + \mathrm{d} S_\text{ext} \geq 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Phi = 0</math>
<math>\mathrm{d} \Psi = 0</math>
<math>S \, \mathrm{d} T - V \, \mathrm{d} P + \sum_{i=1}^N n_i \, \mathrm{d} \mu_i = 0</math>
<math>U \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( {1 \over T} \right) - V \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( -{P \over T} \right) + \sum_{i=1}^{N} n_i \, \mathrm{d} \! \left( -{\mu_i \over T} \right) = 0</math>
<math>\left( {\partial J \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{V,n} = -U</math>
<math>\left( {\partial F \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n} = -S</math>
<math>\left( {\partial Y \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{P,n} = -H</math>
<math>\left( {\partial G \over \partial T} \right)_{-{P \over T},n} = -\Psi_1</math>
<math>\delta Q_V = C_V \, \mathrm{d} T = \mathrm{d} U = T \, \mathrm{d} S</math>
<math>C_V = \left( {\partial U \over \partial T} \right)_{V,n} = -T \left( {\partial^2 F \over \partial T^2} \right)_{V,n}</math>
<math>-T C_V = \left( {\partial S \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{V,n} = -{1 \over T} \left( {\partial^2 J \over \partial {1 \over T}^2} \right)_{V,n}</math>
<math>\delta Q_P = C_P \, \mathrm{d} T = \mathrm{d} H = T \, \mathrm{d} S</math>
<math>C_P = \left( {\partial H \over \partial T} \right)_{P,n} = -T \left( {\partial^2 G \over \partial T^2} \right)_{P,n}</math>
<math>-T C_P = \left( {\partial S \over \partial {1 \over T}} \right)_{P,n} = -{1 \over T} \left( {\partial^2 Y \over \partial {1 \over T}^2} \right)_{P,n}</math>

<math>\mbox{Ei}(x) = \lim_{\delta \to 0} \left[ \int_{-\infty}^{\delta} \frac{e^{t}}{t}\mathrm dt + \int_{\delta}^{x} \frac{e^{t}}{t}\mathrm dt \right]</math>

<math>{\rm Ei}(-x) = - {\rm E}_1(x)</math>

<math>\mbox{li}(x) := \mbox{Ei} (\ln (x))</math>
<math>\mathrm{Ei}(x) = \gamma+\ln |x| + \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{x^k}{k!k} \qquad x \neq 0</math>

<math>{\rm Ei} (x) = \gamma + \ln x + \exp{(x/2)} \sum_{n=1}^\infty \frac{ (-1)^{n-1} x^n} {n! \, 2^{n-1}} \sum_{k=0}^{\lfloor (n-1)/2 \rfloor} \frac{1}{2k+1}</math>
<math>
\mathrm{E_1}(z)=\frac{\exp(-z)}{z}\sum_{n=0}^{N-1} \frac{n!}{(-z)^n}
</math>
<math>{\rm Ein}(x) = \int_0^x \frac{1-e^{-t}}{t} \mathrm dt 
= \sum_{k=1}^\infty \frac{(-1)^{k+1}x^k}{k\; k!}</math>
<math>\mathrm{E_1}(z) = -\gamma-\ln z + {\rm Ein}(z)\qquad |\mathrm{Arg}(z)| &lt; \pi</math>
<math>\mathrm{Ei}(x) = \gamma+\ln x - \mathrm{Ein}(-x)\qquad x&gt;0</math>

<title>Lemma di Jordan</title>
<math>0\leq\theta_1&lt;\theta_2\leq\pi</math>
<math> \lim_{R \rightarrow +\infty}\max_{\theta\in[\theta_1;\theta_2]}|f(Re^{i\theta})|=0,</math>
<math> \lim_{R \rightarrow +\infty} \int_{\gamma_R} f(z)e^{i\omega z} dz=0,</math>
<math>\max_{z\in\gamma_R}\left|f(z)\right|=M_R\Rightarrow\lim_{R\rightarrow+\infty}M_R=0</math>
<math>\gamma_R(t)=Re^{it}</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq\int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2}\left|f(Re^{it})e^{\omega iRe^{it}}iR\right|dt\leq R\int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2}\left|f(Re^{it})\right|\cdot\left|e^{i\omega Re^{it}}\right|dt\leq M_RR\int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2}\left|e^{i\omega Re^{it}}\right|dt</math>
<math>\left|e^{i\omega Re^{it}}\right|=\left|e^{\omega Ri(\cos t+i\sin t)}\right|=\left|e^{\omega R(i\cos t-\sin t)}\right|\leq e^{-\omega R\sin t}</math>
<math>\left|e^{i\omega Re^{it}}\right|=\left|e^{\omega Ri(\cos t+i\sin t)}\right|=\left|e^{\omega R(i\cos t-\sin t)}\right|\leq e^{-\omega R\sin t}</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq M_RR\int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt\leq M_RR\int_0^{\pi}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt=2M_RR\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq M_RR\int_{\theta_1}^{\theta_2}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt\leq M_RR\int_0^{\pi}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt=2M_RR\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt</math>
<math>g(t)=\sin t,\,t\in\bigg[0,\frac{\pi}{2}\bigg]</math>
<math>h(t)=\frac{2}{\pi}t,\,t\in\bigg[0,\frac{\pi}{2}\bigg]</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq 2M_RR\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}}e^{-\omega R\frac{2}{\pi}t}dt=-2M_RR\left[e^{-\omega R\frac{2}{\pi}t}\right]_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}}\cdot\frac{\pi}{2\omega R}=-\frac{\pi}{\omega}M_R\left(e^{-\omega R}-1\right)</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq 2M_RR\int_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}}e^{-\omega R\frac{2}{\pi}t}dt=-2M_RR\left[e^{-\omega R\frac{2}{\pi}t}\right]_0^{\frac{\pi}{2}}\cdot\frac{\pi}{2\omega R}=-\frac{\pi}{\omega}M_R\left(e^{-\omega R}-1\right)</math>
<math>0\leq\lim_{R\rightarrow+\infty}\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq\lim_{R\rightarrow+\infty}-\frac{\pi}{\omega}M_R\left(e^{-\omega R}-1\right)=0</math>
<math>0\leq\lim_{R\rightarrow+\infty}\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq\lim_{R\rightarrow+\infty}-\frac{\pi}{\omega}M_R\left(e^{-\omega R}-1\right)=0</math>
<math>\lim_{R\to+\infty}M_R=0</math>
<math>\bigg|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\bigg|\leq\frac{\pi}{\omega}M_R(1-e^{-\omega R})\leq\frac{\pi}{\omega}M_R</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq M_RR\int_{\pi}^{2\pi}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt=M_RR\int_{-\pi}^0e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt=2M_RR\int^0_{-\frac{\pi}{2}}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt\leq2M_RR\int_{-\frac{\pi}{2}}^0e^{\omega R}dt</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq M_RR\int_{\pi}^{2\pi}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt=M_RR\int_{-\pi}^0e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt=2M_RR\int^0_{-\frac{\pi}{2}}e^{-\omega R\sin t}dt\leq2M_RR\int_{-\frac{\pi}{2}}^0e^{\omega R}dt</math>
<math>0\leq\left|\int_{\gamma_R}f(z)e^{i\omega z}dz\right|\leq\pi e^{\omega R}M_R</math>
<math> \int_{\gamma_R}=\int_{\Gamma}-\int_{\tilde{\gamma}_R}</math>

<title>Equazione di Steinhart-Hart</title>
<math>{1 \over T} = A + B \ln(R) + C [\ln(R)]^3 </math>
<math>{1 \over t_1+273,15} = A + B \ln(R_1) + C (\ln(R_1))^3 </math>
<math>{1 \over t_2+273,15} = A + B \ln(R_2) + C (\ln(R_2))^3 </math>
<math>{1 \over t_3+273,15} = A + B \ln(R_3) + C (\ln(R_3))^3 </math>
<math>L_1=\ln(R_1)</math>
<math>L_2=\ln(R_2)</math>
<math>L_3=\ln(R_3)</math>
<math>Y_1 = {1 \over t_1 + 273,15}</math>
<math>Y_2 = {1 \over t_2 + 273,15}</math>
<math>Y_3 = {1 \over t_3 + 273,15}</math>
<math>\gamma_2={Y_2-Y_1\over L_2-L_1}</math>
<math>\gamma_3={Y_3-Y_1\over L_3-L_1}</math>
<math>\Rightarrow C=\left( { \gamma_3 - \gamma_2 \over L_3 - L_2} \right)\times\left({1 \over L_1 + L_2 + L_3}\right)</math>
<math>\Rightarrow B=\gamma_2 - C \cdot (L_1^2+L_1 \cdot L_2+L_2^2)</math>
<math>\Rightarrow A=Y_1 - (B+L_1^2 \cdot C) \cdot L_1</math>
<math>R = exp\left(\sqrt[3]{x - {y \over 2}} - \sqrt[3]{x + {y \over 2}}\right)</math>
<math>y = {A - {1 \over T} \over C}</math>
<math>x = \sqrt{\left({B \over 3C}\right)^3 + {y^2 \over 4}}</math>

<title>Relazione di Einstein-Smoluchowski</title>
<math> D = \mu \, k_B T </math>
<math> D = \frac{k_B T}{6\pi\,\eta\,r} </math>
<math>D = \mu \frac{k_B T}{q}</math>
<math>F(\mathbf{x})=-\nabla U(\mathbf{x})</math>
<math>v(\mathbf{x})=\mu(\mathbf{x}) F(\mathbf{x})</math>
<math>\mathbf{J}_\mathrm{drift}(\mathbf{x}) = \mu(\mathbf{x}) F(\mathbf{x}) \rho(\mathbf{x}) = -\rho(\mathbf{x}) \mu(\mathbf{x}) \nabla U(\mathbf{x}),</math>
<math>\mathbf{J}_\mathrm{diffusion}(\mathbf{x})=-D(\mathbf{x}) \nabla \rho(\mathbf{x}),</math>
<math>\mathbf{J}_\mathrm{drift} + \mathbf{J}_\mathrm{diffusion} = 0</math>
<math>\nabla\rho = \frac{\mathrm{d}\rho}{\mathrm{d} U} \nabla U.</math>
<math>0 = \mathbf{J}_\mathrm{drift} + \mathbf{J}_\mathrm{diffusion} = -\mu \rho \nabla U - D \nabla \rho = \left(-\mu \rho - D \frac{\mathrm{d}\rho}{\mathrm{d} U}\right)\nabla U.</math>
<math>D = -\mu \frac{\rho}{\frac{\mathrm{d}\rho}{\mathrm{d} U}}.</math>
<math>\rho(\mathbf{x}) = A e^{-\frac{U(\mathbf{x})}{k_B T}},</math>
<math>\frac{\mathrm{d}\rho}{\mathrm{d} U} = -\frac{1}{k_B T}\rho,</math>
<math>D = -\mu \frac{\rho}{\frac{\mathrm{d}\rho}{\mathrm{d} U}} = \mu k_B T,</math>

<title>Identiteit van Euler</title>

      <text xml:space="preserve">De '''identiteit van Euler''', genoemd naar de [[Zwitserland|Zwitserse]] [[wiskundige]] [[Leonhard Euler]], luidt:

:&lt;math&gt;e^{i\pi}+1=0</math>
<math>e^{i\pi}+1=0</math>

<math>e^{i\pi}=\cos(\pi)+i\cdot \sin(\pi)</math>
<math>e^{i\pi}=-1+i\cdot 0</math>
<math>e^{i\pi}+1=0 </math>
<math>e^{i\pi}+1=0</math>

<title>Gaussische functie</title>
<math>f(x) = a e^{-\left(\frac{x-b}{c}\right)^2}</math>
<math>x=b</math>
<math>f(x) = e^{-ax^2}</math>
<math>F(\omega)= \mathcal{F}(f)(\omega) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} \int_{-\infty}^\infty f(x) e^{- i\omega x}\,{\rm d}x </math>
<math>= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} \int_{-\infty}^\infty e^{-ax^2} e^{- i\omega x}\,{\rm d}x </math>
<math>= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} \int_{-\infty}^\infty e^{-ax^2 - i\omega x}\,{\rm d}x </math>
<math>= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} \int_{-\infty}^\infty e^{-\left(\sqrt{a}x+\frac{i \omega}{2\sqrt{a}}\right)^2 + \left(\frac{i \omega}{2\sqrt{a}}\right)^2}\,{\rm d}x </math>
<math>= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-\frac{\omega^2}{4a}} \int_{-\infty}^\infty e^{-\left(\sqrt{a}x+\frac{i \omega}{2\sqrt{a}}\right)^2}\,{\rm d}x </math>
<math>= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2\pi}} e^{-\frac{\omega^2}{4a}} \sqrt{\frac{\pi}{a}}</math>
<math>= \frac{1}{\sqrt{2a}} e^{-\frac{\omega^2}{4a}}</math>

<title>Coble-kruip</title>
<math> met [[Project:AWB|AWB]]</comment>
      <model>wikitext</model>
      <format>text/x-wiki</format>
      <text xml:space="preserve">'''Coble-kruip''' ([[Engels]]: ''Coble creep'') is een vorm van [[diffusiekruip]] in [[kristallijne stof]]fen (stoffen die opgebouwd zijn uit [[Kristal (natuurwetenschappen)|kristallen]], in de [[materiaalkunde]] ook wel [[korrel (kristal)|korrels]] genoemd), waarbij de [[diffusie]] van [[vacancy|vacancies]] aan de [[korrelgrens|korrelgrenzen]] plaatsvindt. Als de stof zich onder een [[differentiaalspanning]] bevindt leidt dit tot een stroom van deeltjes door de korrelgrenzen naar de vlakken van een korrel waar de kleinste [[compressie (geologie)|compressieve]] [[mechanische spanning|spanning]] op staat. Door deze stroming van deeltjes [[deformatie|deformeert]] de korrel.

Coble-kruip is genoemd naar [[Robert Coble]], een [[Verenigde Staten|Amerikaans]] [[materiaalkunde|materiaalkundige]] die in 1963 als eerste over deze vorm van [[kruip]] in materialen [[wetenschappelijke publicatie|publiceerde]].&lt;ref&gt;{{en}}{{aut|[[Robert Coble|Coble, R.L.]]}}; 1963: ''A Model for Boundary Diffusion Controlled Creep in Polycrystalline Materials'', Journal of Applied Physics '''34''', p. 1679.&lt;/ref&gt;

==Vervorming door Coble-kruip==
De snelheid van [[vervorming]] (Engels: ''strain rate'') van een materiaal wordt bij Coble-creep gegeven met de formule:

:&lt;math&gt;\dot{\epsilon} = \frac{\sigma}{d^3} D_C e^{-Q_{Coble}/RT}</math>
<math>\dot{\epsilon} = \frac{\sigma}{d^3} D_C e^{-Q_{Coble}/RT}</math>

<math> r = a \sin\theta \, \cos^2\theta</math>

<title>Scalaire kromming</title>
<math>\operatorname{Ric} = R_{ij}\,dx^i\otimes dx^j.</math>
<math>R = \mbox{tr}_g\,\operatorname{Ric}.</math>
<math>R = g^{ij}R_{ij} \,</math>
<math>R = g^{ab} (\Gamma^c_{ab,c} - \Gamma^c_{ac,b} + \Gamma^d_{ab}\Gamma^c_{cd} - \Gamma^d_{ac} \Gamma^c_{bd})</math>

<title>Интегральная показательная функция</title>
<math>\operatorname{Ei} (x)=\mathrm{v.p.}\int\limits_{-\infty}^x\frac{e^t}{t}\,\mathrm dt
=\gamma+\operatorname{ln}|x|+\sum\limits_{n\ge1}\frac{x^n}{n!\cdot n}, \;  x\in\mathbb R,\; (1)</math>
<math>\operatorname{Ei}(z)=\int\limits_{-\infty}^z\frac{e^t}{t}\,\mathrm dt
=\gamma+\operatorname{ln}(-z)+\sum\limits_{n\ge1}\frac{z^n}{n!\cdot n}, \;  |\arg(-z)|&lt;\pi, \;(2)</math>
<math>t=0</math>
<math>z=0</math>
<math>
\int\limits_0^{+\infty}\frac{e^{ibx}\mathrm dx}{x+iz}=
\begin{cases}
-e^{bz}\operatorname{Ei}(-bz),&amp; \operatorname{arg}z\not\in[\pi/2,\pi],\\
-e^{bz}\left[\operatorname{Ei}(-bz)-2\pi i\right],&amp; \operatorname{arg}z\in(\pi/2,\pi).
\end{cases}\;(2)
</math>
<math>
\int\limits_0^{\infty}\frac{x\cos bx\,\mathrm dx}{x^2+y^2}=
-\frac12\left[e^{|by|}\operatorname{Ei}(-|by|)+e^{-|by|}\operatorname{Ei}_1(|by|)\right],\;(3)</math>
<math>
\operatorname{Ei}_1 (y)=\frac12
\left[\operatorname{Ei}(y+i0)+\operatorname{Ei}(y-i0)\right]
=\gamma+\operatorname{ln}y+\sum\limits_{n\ge 1}\frac{y^n}{n!\cdot n},\; y&gt;0,\;\operatorname{Ei}_1 (y)\in\mathbb R.\;(4)
</math>
<math>
\int_0^\infty\frac{x\sin bx\,\mathrm dx}{x^2+z^2}=\frac\pi2\operatorname{exp}[-bz\operatorname{sign}\Im z],\;b&gt;0.
</math>
<math>
\int_0^\infty\frac{x\cos bx\,\mathrm dx}{x^2+z^2}=
-\frac12\left\{e^{bz}\operatorname{Ei}(-bz)+e^{-bz}\left[\operatorname{Ei}(bz)
+\pi i\operatorname{sign}\Im z\right]\right\},\;b&gt;0,\; \Re z\ne 0.\;(5)
</math>
<math>z=y\pm i0</math>

    1 &amp; \ln\left(R_2\right) &amp; \ln^3\left(R_2\right) \\
    1 &amp; \ln\left(R_3\right) &amp; \ln^3\left(R_3\right)
 \end{bmatrix}\begin{bmatrix}
    A \\
    B \\
    C
 \end{bmatrix} = \begin{bmatrix}
   \frac{1}{T_1} \\
   \frac{1}{T_2} \\
   \frac{1}{T_3}
 \end{bmatrix}
</math>
<math>\begin{align}
            L_1 &amp;= \ln\left(R_1\right),\; L_2 = \ln\left(R_2\right),\; L_3 = \ln\left(R_3\right) \\
            Y_1 &amp;= \frac{1}{T_1},\; Y_2 = \frac{1}{T_2},\; Y_3 = \frac{1}{T_3} \\
       \gamma_2 &amp;= \frac{Y_2 - Y_1}{L_2 - L_1},\; \gamma_3 = \frac{Y_3 - Y_1}{L_3 - L_1} \\
  \Rightarrow C &amp;= \left( \frac{ \gamma_3 - \gamma_2 }{ L_3 - L_2} \right) \left(L_1 + L_2 + L_3\right)^{-1} \\
  \Rightarrow B &amp;= \gamma_2 - C \left(L_1^2 + L_1 L_2 + L_2^2\right) \\
  \Rightarrow A &amp;= Y_1 - \left(B + L_1^2 C\right) L_1
\end{align}</math>

<title>Choque inelástico</title>

-\frac{e}{c} (-i\hbar\boldsymbol\nabla \times \mathbf{A}) = \frac{i\hbar e}{c} \mathbf{B}

<title>Determinante de Hurwitz</title>
<math>P(\lambda)= a_0 \lambda^n + a_1 \lambda^{n-1} + \cdots + a_{n-1} \lambda + a_n</math>
<math>i=0,1,\ldots,n</math>
<math>
H=
\begin{pmatrix}
a_1 &amp; a_3 &amp; a_5 &amp; \dots &amp; \dots &amp; \dots &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 \\
a_0 &amp; a_2 &amp; a_4 &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots \\
0 &amp; a_1 &amp; a_3 &amp; &amp; &amp; &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots \\
\vdots &amp; a_0 &amp; a_2 &amp; \ddots &amp; &amp; &amp; 0 &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots \\
\vdots &amp; 0 &amp; a_1 &amp; &amp; \ddots &amp; &amp; a_n &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots \\

<title>Combinatoria enumerativa</title>
<math>F(x) = \sum^{\infty}_{n=0}f_nx^n</math>
<math>F(x) = \sum^{\infty}_{n=0}f_n\frac{x^n}{n!}</math>
<math>\mbox{Seq}(\mathcal{F}) = \epsilon\ \cup\ \mathcal{F} \ \cup\ \mathcal{F} \times \mathcal{F} \ \cup\ \mathcal{F} \times \mathcal{F} \times \mathcal{F}\  \cup \cdots</math>
<math>1+F(x) + [F(x)]^2 + [F(x)]^3 + \cdots = \frac{1}{1-F(x)}</math>
<math>\mathcal{P} = \{\bullet\} \times \mbox{Seq}(\mathcal{P})</math>
<math>P(x) = x\frac{1}{1-P(x)}</math>
<math>P(x) = \frac{1-\sqrt{1-4x}}{2}</math>
<math>\begin{align}
p_n &amp; = [x^n] P(x) = [x^n] \frac{1-\sqrt{1-4x}}{2} \\[6pt]
&amp; = [x^n] \frac{1}{2} - [x^n] \frac{1}{2} \sqrt{1-4x} \\[6pt]
&amp; = -\frac{1}{2} [x^n] \sum^{\infty}_{k=0} {\frac{1}{2} \choose k} (-4x)^k \\[6pt]
&amp; = -\frac{1}{2} {\frac{1}{2} \choose n} (-4)^n \\[6pt]
&amp; = \frac{1}{n} {2n-2 \choose n-1}
\end{align}</math>

<math>\varphi = \pi</math>
<math>\cos \pi = -1\,</math>
<math>\sin \pi = 0\,</math>
<math>e^{i \pi} = -1\,</math>
<math>e^{i \pi} +1 = 0\,</math>

<title>指数積分</title>
<math>\operatorname{Ei}(x) = -\operatorname{p.\!v.}\int_{-x}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t = \operatorname{p.\!v.}\int_{-\infty}^{x}\frac{e^{t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t</math>
<math>\begin{align}
\operatorname{{Ei}^{real}}(x) &amp;= \lim_{\epsilon\to+0}\left(-\int_{-x}^{-\epsilon}\frac{e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t-\int_{\epsilon}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t\right)\quad &amp;(x&gt;0)\\
\operatorname{{Ei}^{real}}(x) &amp;= -\int_{-x}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t\quad &amp;(x&lt;0)
\end{align}</math>
<math>\operatorname{Ei}(z) = -\pi i + \int_{-\infty-0i}^{1-0i}\frac{e^{t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t + \int_{1}^{z}\frac{e^{t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t</math>
<math>\operatorname{Ei}(x\pm 0i) = \operatorname{{Ei}^{real}}(x)\pm\pi i \quad(x&lt;0), \quad \operatorname{Ei}(x) = \operatorname{{Ei}^{real}}(x) \quad(x&gt;0)</math>
<math>E_n(z) = z^{n-1}\int_{z}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t}}{t^n}\,\operatorname{d}\!t</math>
<math>E_1(z) = \int_{z}^{\infty}\frac{e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t</math>
<math>\begin{align}
&amp;\operatorname{Im}(E_n(x\pm 0i)) = \mp\pi(-x)^{n-1} i \quad(x&lt;0),\quad \operatorname{Im}(E_n(x)) = 0 \quad(x&gt;0) \\
&amp;E_1(x\pm 0i) = -\operatorname{{Ei}^{real}}(-x)\mp\pi i \quad(x&lt;0),\quad E_1(x) = -\operatorname{{Ei}^{real}}(-x) \quad(x&gt;0)
\end{align}</math>
<math>\operatorname{Ei}(z) = -E_1(-z)+\pi i \quad(\operatorname{Im}(z)&lt;0), \quad \operatorname{Ei}(z) = -E_1(-z)-\pi i \quad(\operatorname{Im}(z)&gt;0)</math>
<math>\operatorname{Ein}(z) = \int_{0}^{z} \frac{1-e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t</math>
<math>\begin{align}
\operatorname{Ein}(z) - E_1(z) - \log z &amp;= \int_{0}^{z} \frac{1-e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t - \int_{z}^{\infty} \frac{e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t - \int_{1}^{z} \frac{1}{t}\,\operatorname{d}t \\
&amp;= \int_{0}^{1} \frac{1-e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t - \int_{1}^{\infty} \frac{e^{-t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t \\
&amp;= -\int_{0}^{\infty} (\log t)e^{-t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t \\
&amp;= \gamma
\end{align}</math>
<math>\begin{align}
E_1(z) &amp;= -\gamma-\log z+\operatorname{Ein}(z) \\
\operatorname{Ei}(z) &amp;= \gamma+\log z-\operatorname{Ein}(-z)
\end{align}</math>
<math>\begin{align}
\operatorname{Ein}(z) &amp;= \int_{0}^{z} \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{(-t)^{k-1}}{k!}\,\operatorname{d}\!t \\
&amp;= -\sum_{k=1}^{\infty}\frac{(-z)^k}{k\;k!}
\end{align}</math>
<math>\begin{align}
\operatorname{Ein}(z) &amp;= \int_{0}^{z} e^{-t} \sum_{k=1}^{\infty} \frac{t^{k-1}}{k!}\,\operatorname{d}\!t \\
&amp;= e^{-z} \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \left(\sum_{k=1}^{n} \frac{1}{k}\right) \frac{z^n}{n!} \\
\operatorname{Ein}(z) &amp;= \int_{0}^{z} e^{-t/2} \sum_{k=0}^{\infty} \frac{(t/2)^{2k}}{(2k+1)!}\,\operatorname{d}\!t \\
&amp;= e^{-z/2} \sum_{n=1}^{\infty} \left(\sum_{k=0}^{\lfloor(n-1)/2\rfloor} \frac{2}{2k+1}\right) \frac{(z/2)^n}{n!}
\end{align}</math>
<math>E_1(z) = -e^{-z}\left\{\sum_{k=1}^{n}(k-1)!\left(-\frac{1}{z}\right)^k + O\left(\frac{1}{z^{n+1}}\right)\right\}</math>
<math>\begin{align}
&amp;\operatorname{Si}(z)=\int_{0}^{z}\frac{\sin{t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t\\
&amp;\operatorname{si}(z)=-\int_{z}^{\infty}\frac{\sin{t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t=\operatorname{Si}(z)-\frac{\pi}{2}
\end{align}</math>
<math>\operatorname{Ci}(z)=-\int_{z}^{z+\infty}\frac{\cos{t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t</math>
<math>\begin{align}
\operatorname{Ci}(z) &amp;= \gamma+\log{z}-\operatorname{Cin}(z) \\
\operatorname{Cin}(z) &amp;= \int_{0}^{z}\frac{1-\cos{t}}{t}\,\operatorname{d}\!t
\end{align}</math>
<math>\operatorname{Ein}(\pm iz) = \operatorname{Cin}(z)\pm i\operatorname{Si}(z)</math>
<math>\begin{align}
\operatorname{Li}(z) &amp;= \operatorname{Ei}(\log{z})-\operatorname{Ei}(\log{2}) = \int_{2}^{z}\frac{1}{\log{t}}\,\operatorname{d}\!t \\
\operatorname{li}(z) &amp;= \operatorname{Ei}(\log{z}) = \operatorname{p.\!v.}\int_{0}^{2}\frac{1}{\log{t}}\,\operatorname{d}\!t + \int_{2}^{z}\frac{1}{\log{t}}\,\operatorname{d}\!t
\end{align}</math>

<title>カゾラーティ・ワイエルシュトラスの定理</title>
<math>\mathbb{U}_\delta:=\{z\in\mathbb{C}:\;0&lt;|z-z_0|&lt;\delta\}</math>
<math>f(z)=e^{1/z}</math>
<math>z=\frac{1}{\log v+2{\pi}in},\quad{n\ge\frac{1}{2\pi\delta}+1}</math>
<math>f(z)=v</math>
<math>F(z)=\frac{1}{f(z)-v}</math>
<math>\left|F(z)\right|=\frac{1}{\left|f(z)-v\right|}\le\frac{1}{\epsilon}\qquad\left(z\in\mathbb{U}_\delta\right)</math>
<math>\lim_{z\to z_0}f(z) = v</math>
<math>\lim_{z\to z_0}(z - z_0) F(z) = 0</math>
<math>\forall{z\in\mathbb{U}_\delta},F(z) = G(z)</math>
<math>f(z)=\frac{1}{G(z)}+v\qquad\left(z\in\mathbb{U}_\delta\right)</math>

<title>縮閉線</title>
<math>\boldsymbol{T}(s) = \gamma'(s)</math>
<math>\boldsymbol{T}'(s) = k(s)\boldsymbol{N}(s)</math>
<math>R(s) = \frac{1}{k(s)}</math>
<math>E(s) = \gamma(s) + R(s)\boldsymbol{N}(s) = \gamma(s) + \frac{1}{k(s)}\boldsymbol{N}(s)</math>
<math>(X,Y) = (x,y) + R \boldsymbol{N} = (x-R\sin\varphi,y+R\cos\varphi)</math>
<math>(\cos \varphi, \sin \varphi) = \frac{(x', y')}{(x'^2+y'^2)^{1/2}},\quad R = 1/k = \frac{(x'^2+y'^2)^{3/2}}{x'y''-x''y'}</math>
<math>\begin{cases}
  X[x,y]= x-y'\dfrac{x'^2+y'^2}{x'y''-x''y'}\\[10pt]
  Y[x,y]= y+x'\dfrac{x'^2+y'^2}{x'y''-x''y'}
\end{cases}</math>
<math>
  \int_{s_1}^{s_2}\left|\frac{\mathrm dR}{\mathrm ds}\right| \mathrm ds
</math>
<math>
  \int_{s_1}^{s_2}\left|\frac{\mathrm dR}{\mathrm ds}\right| \mathrm ds = |R(s_2)-R(s_1)|
</math>
<math>
  \frac{\mathrm d\sigma}{\mathrm ds} = \left|\frac{\mathrm dR}{\mathrm ds}\right|
</math>
<math>
  \frac{\mathrm dE}{\mathrm ds} = \frac{\mathrm d\gamma}{\mathrm ds} +\frac{\mathrm dR}{\mathrm ds}\boldsymbol{N}(s) - \boldsymbol{T}(s) = \frac{\mathrm dR}{\mathrm ds}\boldsymbol{N}(s)
</math>
<math>
  \frac{\mathrm dE}{\mathrm d\sigma} = \frac{\mathrm dE}{\mathrm ds}\bigg/\frac{\mathrm d\sigma}{\mathrm ds} = \pm\boldsymbol{N}
</math>
<math>
  \frac{\mathrm d^2E}{\mathrm d\sigma^2}
  = \pm\frac{\mathrm d\boldsymbol{N}}{\mathrm ds}\bigg/\frac{\mathrm d\sigma}{\mathrm ds}
  = -\frac{1}{RR'}\frac{\mathrm dE}{\mathrm d\sigma}
</math>
<math>   k_E = -\frac{1}{RR'} </math>
<math>(X, Y)= \left(-y'\frac{x'^2+y'^2}{x'y''-x''y'},\ x'\frac{x'^2+y'^2}{x'y''-x''y'}\right)</math>

<title>リース平均</title>
<math>s^\delta(\lambda) =

<math>s_n = \sum_{k=0}^n a_n</math>
<math>a_n=1</math>
<math> 
\sum_{n\le \lambda} \left(1-\frac{n}{\lambda}\right)^\delta
= \frac{1}{2\pi i} \int_{c-i\infty}^{c+i\infty} 
\frac{\Gamma(1+\delta)\Gamma(s)}{\Gamma(1+\delta+s)} \zeta(s) \lambda^s \, ds
= \frac{\lambda}{1+\delta} + \sum_n b_n \lambda^{-n}
</math>
<math>a_n=\Lambda(n)</math>
<math> 
\sum_{n\le \lambda} \left(1-\frac{n}{\lambda}\right)^\delta \Lambda(n)
= - \frac{1}{2\pi i} \int_{c-i\infty}^{c+i\infty} 
\frac{\Gamma(1+\delta)\Gamma(s)}{\Gamma(1+\delta+s)} 
\frac{\zeta^\prime(s)}{\zeta(s)} \lambda^s \, ds
= \frac{\lambda}{1+\delta} + 
\sum_\rho \frac {\Gamma(1+\delta)\Gamma(\rho)}{\Gamma(1+\delta+\rho)}
+\sum_n c_n \lambda^{-n}
</math>

<title>非弾性衝突</title>
<math>v_a=\frac{C_R m_b (u_b - u_a) + m_a u_a + m_b u_b} {m_a+m_b}</math>

<title>選点法</title>
<math> y'= f(t,y), \quad y(t_0)=y_0. </math>
<math>\begin{array}{c|ccccc}
  c_1 &amp; a_{11} &amp; a_{12} &amp; \cdots &amp; a_{1n} \\
  c_2 &amp; a_{11} &amp; a_{12} &amp; \cdots &amp; a_{2n} \\
  \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \vdots &amp; \ddots &amp; \vdots \\
  c_n &amp; a_{11} &amp; a_{12} &amp; \cdots &amp; a_{nn} \\ \hline
      &amp; b_1 &amp; b_2 &amp; \cdots &amp; b_n

<math>J=\begin{bmatrix} \frac{\partial(x,y)}{\partial(r,\theta)} \end{bmatrix}</math>

<math>I^2=\int\limits_{-\infty}^{\infty}\int\limits_{-\infty}^{\infty}  e^{-x^2+y^2} dxdy = \int\limits_{0}^{2\pi}\int\limits_{0}^{\infty}  e^{-r^2} rdrd\theta</math>
<math>I^2= \int\limits_{0}^{2\pi}\int\limits_{0}^{\infty}  e^{-r^2} rdrd\theta = \int\limits_{0}^{2\pi} [  e^{-r^2}]_{0}^{\infty} drd\theta =  \int\limits_{0}^{2\pi} \frac{1}{2} d\theta = \pi </math>
<math>I=\sqrt\pi.</math>

<math>\mathbf{a} = (a_1, \dots, a_n)</math>
<math>c = 1</math>

c\rangle</math>

a_i^k</math>

<math>(2x_{1}+2x_{2}+x_{3}) \times 2+(x_{1}+5x_{2}+4x_{3}) \times 1 =5x_{1}+9x_{2}+6x_{3}</math>
<math>(2,2,1)\times 2+(1,5,4) \times 1 =(5,9,6)</math>

<title>LQR控制器</title>
<math>\dot{x} = Ax + Bu</math>
<math>J =  x^T(t_1)F(t_1)x(t_1)  + \int\limits_{t_0}^{t_1} \left( x^T Q x + u^T R u + 2 x^T N u \right) dt</math>
<math>u = -K x \,</math>
<math>K = R^{-1} (B^T P(t) + N^T) \,</math>
<math>A^T P(t) + P(t) A - (P(t) B + N) R^{-1} (B^T P(t) + N^T) + Q = - \dot{P}(t) \,</math>
<math>P(t_1) = F(t_1).</math>
<math>\dot{x} = Ax + Bu</math>
<math>-\dot{\lambda} = Qx + Nu + A^T \lambda </math>
<math> 0 = Ru + N^Tx + B^T \lambda</math>
<math> x(t_0) = x_0</math>
<math> \lambda(t_1) = F(t_1) x(t_1)</math>
<math>\dot{x} = Ax + Bu</math>
<math>J = \int_{0}^\infty \left( x^T Q x + u^T R u + 2 x^T N u \right) dt</math>
<math>u = -K x \,</math>
<math>K = R^{-1} (B^T P + N^T) \,</math>
<math>A^T P + P A - (P B + N) R^{-1} (B^T P + N^T) + Q = 0 \,</math>
<math>\mathcal A^T P + P \mathcal A - P B R^{-1} B^T P + \mathcal Q = 0 \,</math>
<math>\mathcal A = A - B R^{-1} N^T \qquad  \mathcal Q = Q - N R^{-1} N^T \,</math>
<math>x_{k+1} = A x_k + B u_k \,</math>
<math>J = x_N^T Q x_N + \sum\limits_{k=0}^{N-1} \left( x_k^T Q x_k + u_k^T R u_k + 2 x_k^T N u_k \right)</math>
<math>u_k = -F_k x_{k} \,</math>
<math>F_k = (R + B^T P_{k+1} B)^{-1} (B^T P_{k+1} A + N^T) \,</math>
<math>P_{k-1} = A^T P_k A - (A^T P_k B + N) \left( R + B^T P_k B \right)^{-1} (B^T P_k A + N^T) + Q </math>
<math>P_N = Q</math>
<math>x_{k+1} = A x_k + B u_k \,</math>
<math>J = \sum\limits_{k=0}^{\infty} \left( x_k^T Q x_k + u_k^T R u_k + 2 x_k^T N u_k \right)</math>
<math>u_k = -F x_k \,</math>
<math>F = (R + B^T P B)^{-1} (B^T P A + N^T) \,</math>
<math>P = A^T P A - (A^T P B + N) \left( R + B^T P B \right)^{-1} (B^T P A + N^T) + Q </math>
<math>P = \mathcal A^T P \mathcal A - \mathcal A^T P B \left( R + B^T P B \right)^{-1} B^T P \mathcal A + \mathcal Q </math>
<math> \mathcal A = A - B R^{-1} N^T \qquad \mathcal Q = Q - N R^{-1} N^T </math>
